carborough, Toronto|Scarborough]] || 1970-1972 || Folded\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Scarborough Young Bruins]]''' || [[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough]] || 1976-1979 || Folded\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[St. Michael's Buzzers]]''' || [[Toronto]] || 1956-1995 || Joined [[OJHL|OPJHL]]\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Shelburne Wolves]]''' || [[Shelburne, Ontario|Shelburne]] || 1995-1998 || Joined [[OJHL|OPJHL]]\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Syracuse Stars Jr. A|Syracuse Jr. Crunch]]''' || [[Syracuse, New York|Syracuse]] || 1995-1998 || Joined [[OJHL|OPJHL]]\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Thornhill Rattlers]]''' || [[Thornhill, Ontario|Thornhill]] || 1989-1998 || Joined [[OJHL|OPJHL]]\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Toronto Nationals (1970\u20131980)|Toronto Nationals]]''' || [[Toronto]] || 1970-1980 || Folded\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Toronto Red Wings]]''' || [[Toronto]] || 1973-1979 || Folded\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Wellington Dukes]]''' || [[Wellington, Ontario|Wellington]] || 1989-1998 || Joined [[OJHL|OPJHL]]\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Weston Dodgers]]''' || [[Weston, Toronto|Weston]] || 1956-1972 || Joined [[Ontario Provincial Junior A Hockey League (1972-1987)|OPJHL]]\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''[[Wexford Raiders]]''' || [[Wexford, Toronto|Wexford]] || 1972-1998 || Joined [[OJHL|OPJHL]]\n|}\n|}\n\n==Champions==\n''Please note: On the chart, the bolded team is the league champion.''\n\n{| cellpadding=\"1\" width=\"350px\" style=\"font-size: 90%; border: 1px solid gray;\" \n| \n{| cellpadding=\"1\" width=\"350px\" style=\"font-size: 90%;\" \n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"background: #ADD8E6;\" width=\"30\" |'''Year'''\n! style=\"background: #ADD8E6;\" width=\"177\" |'''Champion'''\n! style=\"background: #ADD8E6;\" width=\"177\" |'''Finalist'''\n|- align=\"center\"\n|1951   ||'''[[Weston Dukes]]'''    ||Brampton Regents\n|- align=\"center\"\n|1952   ||'''[[Weston Dukes]]'''    ||St. Michael's Buzzers\n|- align=\"center\"\n|1953   ||'''[[Weston Dukes]]'''    ||